HEADWORD: Scotomy
<hw>Scot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>scotomia</ets>, from Gr. <?/ dizziness, fr. <?/ to darken, fr.
<grk>sko`tos</grk> darkness: cf. F. <ets>scotomie</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Dizziness with dimness of sight.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Massinger.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Obscuration of the field of vision
due to the appearance of a dark spot before the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scotoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
